article.headline: Silver Stars win at Houston for second road win
article.linkText: Silver Stars shine bright in road win vs. Comets
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Shannon Johnson went 11-for-11 from the free
throw line and scored 18 points to lead San Antonio to a 68-63 win
over the Houston Comets on Saturday, the Silver Stars' second road
win of the season.

"It was important for us to play well together today because we
knew the Comets were going to be tough," Johnson said. "(Going)
11-for-11 is pretty good considering I was just 1-for-6 the other
night."

Bernadette Ngoyisa tied her season high with 10 points as the
Silver Stars beat Houston for the first time in four tries this
season and improved to 2-12 on the road.

"I'm pleased with how we played because we were able to put two
really good halves together," San Antonio coach Dan Hughes said.
"I feel the Comets are a team that could win the championship, but
we competed and our execution was consistent throughout."

Sheryl Swoopes scored 17 points for the Comets who have dropped
three straight at home. Tina Thompson added 17 points for Houston,
which has not won at the Toyota Center since a 58-54 win over
Sacramento on July 19.

"We tried to contain Swoopes and Thompson," Johnson said. "We
know that they are going to get theirs, but we wanted to make sure
no one else could beat us."

After trailing most of the game, Houston took its first lead
since 12-10 when Swoopes converted a three-point play with 13:37
left. Swoopes capped a 13-5 run after bouncing the ball off a
defender, retaking control and then laying the ball in while being
fouled. But the Silver Stars responded with a 14-5 run to take a
59-53 lead with 4:44 left in the game. They never trailed again.

"I think we should be concerned about this loss, but we need to
look at what we did wrong today and work on that," Thompson added.
"But it just comes down to us not making our shots."

Wendy Palmer Daniel added 11 points for San Antonio, which had
lost six straight games away from home.
